1
00:00:20,916 --> 00:00:23,458
I told you from our first date

2
00:00:23,666 --> 00:00:25,958
not to bring anyone with you.

3
00:00:26,166 --> 00:00:29,166
Instead you bring your brother,
your sister, your nephew,

4
00:00:29,375 --> 00:00:33,416
we are never alone,
we are always in three!

5
00:00:33,625 --> 00:00:37,500
You promised me:
"Tomorrow, who knows..."

6
00:00:37,708 --> 00:00:42,458
"It'll be only me... with my mother!"

7
00:00:44,791 --> 00:00:49,708
You, your mom, and I
walking around Toledo.

8
00:00:49,916 --> 00:00:53,458
We walk ahead
and you mother walks behind us.

9
00:00:53,666 --> 00:00:55,500
You, your mom, and I.

10
00:00:55,708 --> 00:00:58,916
Always together.
It's crazy!

11
00:00:59,125 --> 00:01:02,541
She even came on our honeymoon!

12
00:01:02,750 --> 00:01:05,833
When we go to the movies or dancing,
and we try to make out

13
00:01:06,041 --> 00:01:09,916
like a policeman
she's always there and stops us.

14
00:01:11,041 --> 00:01:14,125
But I'm in love,

15
00:01:14,333 --> 00:01:16,958
so I have given up on this.

16
00:01:17,166 --> 00:01:19,500
I don't fight this anymore.

17
00:01:19,708 --> 00:01:21,708
You, your mom, and I.

18
00:01:21,916 --> 00:01:24,208
What consolation!
You, your mom, and I.

19
00:01:24,416 --> 00:01:28,458
I'm done with this problem!
You, your mom, and I.

20
00:01:28,666 --> 00:01:30,833
Saint Genaro gave me a miracle.

21
00:01:31,041 --> 00:01:33,416
The other day
she couldn't get out of bed.

22
00:01:33,625 --> 00:01:36,416
She had a fever,
it looked like she was dying.

23
00:01:36,625 --> 00:01:40,791
I almost believed that
just the two of us would go out.

24
00:01:41,000 --> 00:01:44,458
Then I heard
your mother's little voice.

25
00:01:44,666 --> 00:01:49,500
"The little girl will go with you."

26
00:01:51,833 --> 00:01:57,000
Me, your sister and you
went to bar Chiatamone.

27
00:01:57,208 --> 00:02:01,166
"Do you want
an ice cream or a drink?"

28
00:02:01,375 --> 00:02:03,500
Whatever costs more!

29
00:02:03,708 --> 00:02:05,708
As a souvenir of that day,

30
00:02:05,916 --> 00:02:09,750
at the Villa they took our picture.

31
00:02:09,958 --> 00:02:12,791
She wanted a balloon, a sweet,
and she didn't want to walk!

32
00:02:13,000 --> 00:02:16,000
I looked at her and I thought
to throw her in the sea!

33
00:02:18,125 --> 00:02:21,125
I gave up.

34
00:02:21,333 --> 00:02:23,875
I am in love.

35
00:02:24,083 --> 00:02:26,583
I don't fight it anymore.

36
00:02:26,791 --> 00:02:28,958
My love,
you are always with your family.

37
00:02:29,166 --> 00:02:33,333
Your family is more like a tribe.
They come from Milan, from the east.

38
00:02:33,541 --> 00:02:36,958
And all these people
are always around!

39
00:02:37,166 --> 00:02:41,000
An old aunt who lives in CefalÃ¹

40
00:02:41,208 --> 00:02:45,708
came here and she never left!

41
00:02:47,500 --> 00:02:49,916
Me, your aunt and you.

42
00:02:50,125 --> 00:02:52,833
Poor one, she is sickly,

43
00:02:53,041 --> 00:02:56,333
every now and then she faints.

44
00:02:56,541 --> 00:02:58,458
Me, your aunt and you.

45
00:02:58,666 --> 00:03:01,041
Fresh eggs, mozzarella.

46
00:03:01,250 --> 00:03:04,000
We only go around by carriage!

47
00:03:05,000 --> 00:03:08,000
I am paying for everything,
who is going to pay me back?

48
00:03:08,208 --> 00:03:11,500
It's either I dump you now,
or next month I'll be broke.

49
00:03:12,791 --> 00:03:18,333
You put me in troubles,
I should marry another one.

50
00:03:18,541 --> 00:03:20,875
I don't wanna see you ever again.

51
00:03:21,083 --> 00:03:23,250
You, you mom, and I.

52
00:03:23,458 --> 00:03:26,958
Me, your father,
your brother, your sister.

53
00:03:27,166 --> 00:03:30,291
- Freedom is here!
- No, Mrs. Amalia!

54
00:03:30,500 --> 00:03:32,791
I'm getting free!

55
00:03:33,000 --> 00:03:37,000
You could never
find a mother like me!

56
00:03:37,208 --> 00:03:41,375
Mrs. Amalia, you're not a mother,
you are two mothers,

57
00:03:41,583 --> 00:03:45,166
two mother-in-law's,
all the mother-in-law's in the world!

58
00:03:45,375 --> 00:03:50,041
Before you speak to me
rinse your mouth out with rosewater!

59
00:03:50,250 --> 00:03:52,958
We nurtured a viper in our bosom.

60
00:03:53,166 --> 00:03:57,458
You shut up!
You're not worthy of naming vipers!

61
00:03:57,666 --> 00:03:59,458
They are holy animals of God.

62
00:03:59,666 --> 00:04:02,708
You promised to take me
to the sanctuary in Pompeii!

63
00:04:02,916 --> 00:04:07,833
Aunt Maria, walk to Pompeii,
like the pilgrims.

64
00:04:08,416 --> 00:04:13,666
Nicolino, if you want to go, go,
but you will find me in the hospital!

65
00:04:13,875 --> 00:04:16,833
- I will kill myself!
- Move it!

66
00:04:17,041 --> 00:04:20,458
- I want to kill myself!
- Move it.

67
00:04:20,666 --> 00:04:23,291
Nicolino left
and he's never coming back!

68
00:04:23,500 --> 00:04:25,583
He's never coming back!

69
00:04:27,541 --> 00:04:30,416
It's over.

70
00:04:31,416 --> 00:04:33,083
It's over.

71
00:04:33,291 --> 00:04:35,916
I am sorry for her.

72
00:04:36,708 --> 00:04:39,125
What do I care?

73
00:04:39,333 --> 00:04:41,958
I'll marry an orphan
and I'll do something good.

74
00:04:42,166 --> 00:04:44,750
Above all else I'll have some peace.

75
00:04:44,958 --> 00:04:46,500
Good evening.

76
00:05:02,375 --> 00:05:06,083
- Hi, Gaetano.
- Nicolino, so you're not dead!

77
00:05:06,291 --> 00:05:08,041
I haven't seen you in four shows!

78
00:05:08,250 --> 00:05:11,875
Now you will see me more,
I broke up with the mother.

79
00:05:13,708 --> 00:05:15,958
- With the mother?
- The mother, Carmelina...

80
00:05:16,166 --> 00:05:21,041
In this country, to be
engaged is like being a slave.

81
00:05:21,250 --> 00:05:24,958
Fortunately you understood this.
Now you are free and relaxed.

82
00:05:25,166 --> 00:05:27,791
- Framing!
- Damn!

83
00:05:30,833 --> 00:05:33,666
You can't relax for
one minute in this movie theater.

84
00:05:37,250 --> 00:05:39,625
Nicolino, you did good.

85
00:05:39,833 --> 00:05:41,666
Here, drink some wine.

86
00:05:41,875 --> 00:05:43,875
What are you doing?

87
00:05:44,083 --> 00:05:46,958
Don Gaetano, what are you doing?
Sleeping?

88
00:05:47,166 --> 00:05:49,166
- What?
- It's still the first part.

89
00:05:49,375 --> 00:05:51,708
- And so?
- We've already seen this!

90
00:05:51,916 --> 00:05:54,208
You'll understand the story better.

91
00:05:54,416 --> 00:05:57,333
You are ignorant,
you need to see things twice!

92
00:05:57,541 --> 00:06:01,916
- What now?
- Wait for the end of the movie. Go.

93
00:06:05,083 --> 00:06:07,291
Nicolino, what are you thinking?

94
00:06:07,500 --> 00:06:12,041
Without Carmelina,
I'm better off dead.

95
00:06:12,250 --> 00:06:14,541
What did the bus driver
ever do to you?

96
00:06:14,750 --> 00:06:18,500
If you want to ruin yourself,
marry her.

97
00:06:18,708 --> 00:06:20,708
Easy for you to say!

98
00:06:20,916 --> 00:06:23,916
Her mother told me:
"Carmelina is still a little girl".

99
00:06:24,125 --> 00:06:27,916
"Only after three years can
you know each other well enough."

100
00:06:28,125 --> 00:06:31,208
Not even a marriage last three years!

101
00:06:31,416 --> 00:06:34,000
And she says
I don't have a steady job.

102
00:06:34,208 --> 00:06:36,708
Does she know
that you run this movie theater?

103
00:06:36,916 --> 00:06:41,125
She hates movie theaters,
she prefers TV.

104
00:06:41,333 --> 00:06:42,708
How disgusting!

105
00:06:42,916 --> 00:06:46,000
- Who does she want for her girl?
- I know!

106
00:06:47,083 --> 00:06:48,666
GiosuÃ¨ ruined me.

107
00:06:48,875 --> 00:06:52,958
GiosuÃ¨ had arms
as big as roller coasters!

108
00:06:53,166 --> 00:06:57,250
I don't like them,
they make me sick.

109
00:06:57,458 --> 00:07:01,083
You have to marry a strong man,
a sailor like your dad.

110
00:07:01,291 --> 00:07:03,916
Nicolino is strong,
he's stronger than dad

111
00:07:04,125 --> 00:07:06,208
and he doesn't have any ugly tattoos.

112
00:07:06,416 --> 00:07:10,833
Ungrateful. How dare you
offend your dad's tattoos?

113
00:07:11,041 --> 00:07:12,708
She's killing me.

114
00:07:12,916 --> 00:07:16,500
Instead of arguing come
to the table. It's getting cold!

115
00:07:16,708 --> 00:07:19,958
- I'll still eat it.
- Amalia, let her be.

116
00:07:20,166 --> 00:07:22,916
Carmelina didn't want to offend him.

117
00:07:23,125 --> 00:07:27,500
Annunziata, you know what
the rose tattoo means to me.

118
00:07:27,708 --> 00:07:30,166
You told me many times!

119
00:07:30,375 --> 00:07:32,791
- You are the rose.
- He got the tattoo

120
00:07:33,000 --> 00:07:36,083
so I could always be with him.

121
00:07:36,291 --> 00:07:38,666
They don't make men
like that anymore!

122
00:07:38,875 --> 00:07:42,833
They all died with him
in that shipwreck.

123
00:07:43,041 --> 00:07:45,041
May they rest in peace.
Some more.

124
00:07:45,250 --> 00:07:47,041
- Yes.
- Today these poor girls

125
00:07:47,250 --> 00:07:51,125
have to sacrifice with
these scrawny men that are left.

126
00:07:51,333 --> 00:07:53,500
Nicolino is one of the good ones.

127
00:07:53,708 --> 00:07:56,750
I don't want to end up
like an old hag like aunt Maria!

128
00:07:56,958 --> 00:08:00,208
You'd wish to end up like me.
I'm a respectable woman.

129
00:08:00,416 --> 00:08:03,458
I never got married
because I always hated men.

130
00:08:03,666 --> 00:08:06,375
Mom says that you were born a hag.

131
00:08:06,583 --> 00:08:08,833
- Did you say that?
- It's not true!

132
00:08:09,041 --> 00:08:11,250
It's too much! It's too much!

133
00:08:11,458 --> 00:08:13,250
- Maria...
- I'm leaving.

134
00:08:13,458 --> 00:08:16,458
- Why?
- I'm going back to Benevento.

135
00:08:17,916 --> 00:08:21,458
Maria, what are you doing?
You know that we love you!

136
00:08:21,666 --> 00:08:23,708
Ugly gossiper!

137
00:08:27,750 --> 00:08:31,333
Now that we got that all out,
we are finished eating.

138
00:08:31,541 --> 00:08:34,791
Carmelina, I helped your mother
bring you into this world.

139
00:08:35,000 --> 00:08:37,000
I want to help you stay in it.

140
00:08:37,208 --> 00:08:39,916
Eat a chicken leg. It's so good!

141
00:08:42,666 --> 00:08:48,958
Without Nicolino,
chicken just isn't chicken.

142
00:08:52,291 --> 00:08:55,208
Even the house, the furniture.

143
00:08:55,416 --> 00:08:57,458
I even bought the curtains.

144
00:08:58,583 --> 00:09:01,583
The chandelier
Carmelina really liked.

145
00:09:02,458 --> 00:09:05,208
How horrible! I don't like it.

146
00:09:08,375 --> 00:09:10,375
Love makes you do weird things!

147
00:09:10,583 --> 00:09:15,500
Everything in the house was all
that a married couple could ask for.

148
00:09:15,708 --> 00:09:19,541
There was everything,
only she was missing.

149
00:09:20,583 --> 00:09:23,291
No, an ashtray was missing!
Everything was missing.

150
00:09:23,500 --> 00:09:26,916
Why do I care?
Let's burn this cursed house down!

151
00:09:30,708 --> 00:09:32,666
Who's bothering me?

152
00:09:40,958 --> 00:09:43,083
- Nicolino!
- What are you doing?

153
00:09:43,291 --> 00:09:46,041
I came to stay here.
I don't want you to be alone.

154
00:09:46,250 --> 00:09:49,125
- I'll sacrifice and live with you.
- You can't.

155
00:09:49,333 --> 00:09:53,083
- Carmelina will live here.
- You two got into an argument!

156
00:09:53,291 --> 00:09:56,166
- Yes, but...
- Where will we sleep?

157
00:09:56,375 --> 00:09:58,916
There's only one bed.

158
00:09:59,125 --> 00:10:01,666
- We'll figure it out!
- Gaetano...

159
00:10:01,875 --> 00:10:05,916
Listen. If you want to stay here,
you can sleep in the living room.

160
00:10:06,875 --> 00:10:12,583
- You can't sleep in the bed.
- The wool will get ruined.

161
00:10:12,791 --> 00:10:16,000
What do I care? I'm ruined,
it will be the same for the wool!

162
00:10:16,208 --> 00:10:19,125
Gaetano, I am suffering a lot!

163
00:10:20,583 --> 00:10:23,541
Nicolino, you suffer because
you want to suffer.

164
00:10:23,750 --> 00:10:27,791
If I was her fiancÃ©,
this wool would be fine!

165
00:10:28,000 --> 00:10:30,375
Gaetano, go away!

166
00:10:30,583 --> 00:10:33,875
Carmelina is a serious girl.

167
00:10:34,833 --> 00:10:38,625
Do you remember the movie
we showed last week?

168
00:10:38,833 --> 00:10:40,708
And so?

169
00:10:40,916 --> 00:10:43,500
There were two lovers
that wanted to get married

170
00:10:43,708 --> 00:10:46,583
but the parents didn't
want them to. And...

171
00:10:47,833 --> 00:10:52,416
The parents were forced to let them
get married. Understand?

172
00:10:52,625 --> 00:10:57,166
- They were forced.
- She's not that kind of girl.

173
00:10:57,375 --> 00:11:00,916
I don't care if it's true or not,
but we should make a threat.

174
00:11:01,125 --> 00:11:03,750
All you have to say is:

175
00:11:03,958 --> 00:11:07,666
"Let us marry now, or we'll have
a wedding and baptism together."

176
00:11:07,875 --> 00:11:12,000
But now I don't have the courage
to go near that house.

177
00:11:12,208 --> 00:11:16,208
If you don't submit to her mother,
then it's better that you forget her.

178
00:11:16,416 --> 00:11:18,875
"Every good thing
comes with a bad side".

179
00:11:19,083 --> 00:11:22,625
Says the guy who's mother-in-law died
then he had to pay for her funeral.

180
00:11:23,708 --> 00:11:28,333
Mom, I don't want to eat. I want
to die of hunger like Count Ugolino.

181
00:11:28,541 --> 00:11:30,250
You don't want to eat?

182
00:11:30,458 --> 00:11:34,041
Aunt Maria invited us over
so that we could make up!

183
00:11:34,250 --> 00:11:36,125
Do it for me, Carmelina.

184
00:11:36,333 --> 00:11:38,916
It was very difficult for me
to come here with you.

185
00:11:39,125 --> 00:11:42,208
I'm still not going to eat. I want
to end up like Count Ugolino!

186
00:11:42,416 --> 00:11:46,291
Who is he?
Do you know something about him?

187
00:11:46,500 --> 00:11:50,750
I don't know him. The Aristocrats
are going through a tough time.

188
00:11:50,958 --> 00:11:54,041
- Mom, I'll eat.
- I don't care if you eat.

189
00:11:54,250 --> 00:11:56,666
Careful, you'll end up in the sea!

190
00:11:56,875 --> 00:11:58,916
Let's start eating.

191
00:11:59,125 --> 00:12:03,083
You're going to act like this
over that silly man!

192
00:12:03,291 --> 00:12:08,458
Are we ever going to eat?
I'm going to start eating.

193
00:12:08,666 --> 00:12:10,666
- Something to eat?
- Of course.

194
00:12:10,875 --> 00:12:13,333
- Fish soup.
- I'll take spaghetti and clams.

195
00:12:13,541 --> 00:12:17,166
- Good. Miss?
- Spaghetti and fish soup.

196
00:12:17,375 --> 00:12:19,666
- I'll bring them out together?
- Together.

197
00:12:19,875 --> 00:12:22,958
- Do you have lasagne?
- Of course.

198
00:12:23,250 --> 00:12:26,833
Two spaghetti with clams,
two fish soup and one lasagne.

199
00:12:27,041 --> 00:12:29,666
There's lasagne!

200
00:12:29,875 --> 00:12:33,125
I want to cancel one spaghetti
and I'll take the lasagne.

201
00:12:33,333 --> 00:12:35,708
I want lasagne as well,
cancel one soup.

202
00:12:35,916 --> 00:12:39,125
- I will cancel one fish soup.
- No, don't.

203
00:12:39,333 --> 00:12:41,875
I'll take her fish soup
instead of the lasagne.

204
00:12:42,083 --> 00:12:44,958
If Carmelina doesn't want to eat,
too bad for her.

205
00:12:45,166 --> 00:12:48,416
Carmelina wants to eat.
She's going to eat!

206
00:12:48,625 --> 00:12:51,375
She's hungry, food is coming.

207
00:12:51,583 --> 00:12:55,125
- That's all that was needed!
- Nicolino!

208
00:12:55,333 --> 00:12:58,041
Come here.
What are you doing here?

209
00:12:58,250 --> 00:13:00,875
Do you want to argue in public?

210
00:13:01,083 --> 00:13:05,250
I came here to apologize to you.

211
00:13:05,458 --> 00:13:07,500
You have some nerve!

212
00:13:07,708 --> 00:13:10,666
I know I was wrong,
but I want to make it right.

213
00:13:10,875 --> 00:13:14,166
- I am your humble son.
- What son are you talking about?

214
00:13:14,375 --> 00:13:17,000
You are not part of my family.

215
00:13:17,208 --> 00:13:21,208
Remember that
Carmelina has to eat.

216
00:13:22,500 --> 00:13:25,375
I can't live without you all,
I love you.

217
00:13:25,583 --> 00:13:28,791
Me? He's totally crazy!

218
00:13:29,000 --> 00:13:31,291
- Do you love me?
- Yes.

219
00:13:31,500 --> 00:13:34,833
You, Sisinella, Aunt Maria.
I love you all!

220
00:13:35,041 --> 00:13:37,083
I'm so used to being with you all.

221
00:13:37,291 --> 00:13:40,708
Yesterday I was walking by myself
and I felt like I was naked!

222
00:13:40,916 --> 00:13:44,958
Let him kiss your hand and we
won't worry about it ever again.

223
00:13:45,416 --> 00:13:50,291
OK, I want to be good,
blood isn't water.

224
00:13:50,500 --> 00:13:52,958
- I don't want my daughter to die.
- Good job!

225
00:13:53,166 --> 00:13:55,625
- Let's go.
- Let's go eat.

226
00:13:56,291 --> 00:14:00,708
What's this?
Hands to yourself. Let's go.!

227
00:14:00,916 --> 00:14:03,333
Let's go. Let's sit there.

228
00:14:03,541 --> 00:14:07,250
Finally we can eat.
I've been looking forward to it!

229
00:14:08,500 --> 00:14:11,500
Not there. Aunt Maria at the
head of the table, you sit there.

230
00:14:11,708 --> 00:14:14,166
The ladies already ordered.
What would you like?

231
00:14:14,375 --> 00:14:16,833
- Tortellini with meat sauce.
- Tortellini...

232
00:14:17,041 --> 00:14:19,458
I'll also take the tortellini.

233
00:14:19,666 --> 00:14:21,750
Also for me the tortellini.

234
00:14:21,958 --> 00:14:24,916
- I would like ice cream.
- Ok, after we will get ice cream.

235
00:14:25,125 --> 00:14:27,750
Hold on, calm down, ladies!

236
00:14:27,958 --> 00:14:31,750
Speak one at a time,
or I can't understand anything.

237
00:14:31,958 --> 00:14:34,875
You asked for three fish soups

238
00:14:35,083 --> 00:14:37,583
but now you want three tortellini.

239
00:14:37,791 --> 00:14:39,833
One spaghetti and one lasagne.

240
00:14:40,041 --> 00:14:44,291
We have few minutes.
Listen to what I'm about to say.

241
00:14:44,500 --> 00:14:49,375
- You're about to have a child.
- What are you saying?

242
00:14:50,000 --> 00:14:51,958
- Are you ok?
- Yes.

243
00:14:52,166 --> 00:14:54,458
Did you understand
what we ordered?

244
00:14:54,666 --> 00:14:57,750
Yes. Three tortellini,
two lasagne and one fish soup.

245
00:14:57,958 --> 00:15:00,500
For the young lady...
Where is the young lady?

246
00:15:00,708 --> 00:15:04,458
Carmelina, order something to eat!

247
00:15:04,666 --> 00:15:08,416
- Scrambled eggs.
- This is all scrambled!

248
00:15:08,625 --> 00:15:11,833
I want scrambled eggs,
and also tortellini and fish soup.

249
00:15:12,041 --> 00:15:14,875
I'd take that as well,
but my liver hurts!

250
00:15:15,083 --> 00:15:18,041
- Who ordered liver?
- You didn't understand anything!

251
00:15:18,250 --> 00:15:21,625
No one ordered the liver.

252
00:15:23,250 --> 00:15:26,958
You do what I say.
They will have to submit.

253
00:15:27,166 --> 00:15:29,583
You're going to get me in trouble!

254
00:15:29,791 --> 00:15:32,583
You have to do it for
our love, for our happiness.

255
00:15:32,791 --> 00:15:35,458
I wrote down what I wanted to tell you.

256
00:15:35,916 --> 00:15:37,625
This is the fruit...

257
00:15:37,833 --> 00:15:39,625
The fruit in this hand...

258
00:15:40,541 --> 00:15:44,125
Here in the womb of your daughter
is the fruit of her love.

259
00:15:44,333 --> 00:15:46,166
I knew it!

260
00:15:47,500 --> 00:15:50,875
Mom, in the womb of your daughter

261
00:15:51,083 --> 00:15:53,250
is the fruit of her love!

262
00:15:53,458 --> 00:15:56,208
The sweet fruit of a sour love.

263
00:15:56,833 --> 00:15:58,375
Why is it sour?

264
00:15:58,583 --> 00:16:01,833
Hey! What are you doing?

265
00:16:02,041 --> 00:16:04,250
That's bad manners.

266
00:16:04,458 --> 00:16:07,916
Carmelina is talking to herself,
she's saying she has a fruit.

267
00:16:08,125 --> 00:16:10,458
What fruit?

268
00:16:10,666 --> 00:16:12,916
She must've eaten it,
she says it's sweet.

269
00:16:13,125 --> 00:16:14,875
Sweet?

270
00:16:15,083 --> 00:16:18,541
For a moment of happiness.

271
00:16:18,750 --> 00:16:23,208
How much I suffer!

272
00:16:23,416 --> 00:16:25,583
How much... No!

273
00:16:25,791 --> 00:16:30,666
How much does one have to pay
for a moment of happiness!

274
00:16:31,833 --> 00:16:35,000
What a scandal! Amalia, my sister.

275
00:16:35,208 --> 00:16:38,458
- Be strong, be calm.
- What happened?

276
00:16:38,666 --> 00:16:40,666
Carmelina has a fruit in her womb.

277
00:16:40,875 --> 00:16:43,333
- What fruit?
- The sweet one that was sour.

278
00:16:43,541 --> 00:16:46,291
- Is this a joke?
- What is a womb?

279
00:16:46,500 --> 00:16:49,958
Carmelina has a stomach ache?

280
00:16:50,166 --> 00:16:54,083
- It's not a stomach ache! I wish.
- What is it?

281
00:16:54,291 --> 00:16:57,291
- You have to stay calm.
- I am really calm.

282
00:16:57,500 --> 00:17:00,375
- What are you talking about?
- Try to understand.

283
00:17:00,583 --> 00:17:04,458
I am not married, certain things
are a sin just to think about!

284
00:17:04,666 --> 00:17:08,416
Mom, Carmelina ate
the fruit that Nicolino gave her.

285
00:17:08,625 --> 00:17:11,541
Be quiet, gossiper!
You should mind your own business.

286
00:17:11,750 --> 00:17:16,583
And I don't.
Carmelina ate the fruit!

287
00:17:16,791 --> 00:17:20,458
There, in the womb of your daughter,
is the fruit of her love.

288
00:17:20,666 --> 00:17:24,500
The sweet fruit of a sour love.
What suffering!

289
00:17:24,708 --> 00:17:29,875
How much does one has
to pay for a moment of happiness.

290
00:17:30,083 --> 00:17:34,791
Suffering! The price is too
high for a moment of love.

291
00:17:35,000 --> 00:17:38,333
Wretched soul! What are you saying?

292
00:17:38,541 --> 00:17:41,791
- Nothing. I'm not saying anything.
- Nothing?

293
00:17:42,000 --> 00:17:44,750
Aren't you embarrassed to
say these things at your age?

294
00:17:44,958 --> 00:17:47,916
- What is this silliness?
- It's not silliness.

295
00:17:48,125 --> 00:17:51,166
- Then what is it?
- The truth.

296
00:17:51,375 --> 00:17:55,708
The truth? You are still
a little girl! It's not possible.

297
00:17:55,916 --> 00:17:59,000
I'm not a little girl anymore,
I'm a woman.

298
00:17:59,208 --> 00:18:03,791
- Wait, now I'm even a mother.
- Virgin Mary!

299
00:18:04,000 --> 00:18:06,166
What are you saying?

300
00:18:06,375 --> 00:18:11,041
Who is the fruit vendor?

301
00:18:11,250 --> 00:18:15,291
Mom, I only know one man.
My Nicolino!

302
00:18:15,541 --> 00:18:18,708
Nicolino! Again Nicolino
in front of my eyes!

303
00:18:18,916 --> 00:18:21,708
My God,
I can't deal with this anymore...

304
00:18:21,916 --> 00:18:23,916
Amalia!

305
00:18:24,125 --> 00:18:26,083
Amalia, Amalia!

306
00:18:27,166 --> 00:18:29,166
- Hi, Sisinella.
- Come in, come in.

307
00:18:29,375 --> 00:18:31,416
- Talk to mom!
- Why?

308
00:18:31,625 --> 00:18:36,000
You gave fruit to Carmelina
and now she has a stomach ache.

309
00:18:36,208 --> 00:18:40,125
- What?
- I know everything. Mom even fainted!

310
00:18:40,333 --> 00:18:44,333
- So Carmelina has decided!
- Don't touch me.

311
00:18:44,541 --> 00:18:47,041
Mom, wake up.
I'll tell you the truth.

312
00:18:47,250 --> 00:18:49,250
Mom! Mom!

313
00:18:51,250 --> 00:18:53,916
- Amalia!
- Mom, wake up.

314
00:18:54,125 --> 00:18:57,125
- Oh God!
- See what happened?

315
00:18:57,333 --> 00:19:00,125
- Hurry up, give me a kiss.
- Nicolino, are you crazy?

316
00:19:00,333 --> 00:19:03,791
- Have some respect for my mother.
- Give me a kiss!

317
00:19:04,000 --> 00:19:05,833
Mom, wake up!

318
00:19:06,041 --> 00:19:09,166
Nicolino is trying to kiss Amalia.

319
00:19:09,375 --> 00:19:12,541
- Where is he?
- Here I am. At your service.

320
00:19:12,750 --> 00:19:16,916
Disgraceful, rascal, idiot!

321
00:19:17,125 --> 00:19:21,000
You ruined my daughter,
our home, our family. Everything!

322
00:19:21,208 --> 00:19:25,708
Stay calm. I'm not running away,
I'll take my responsibility.

323
00:19:25,916 --> 00:19:28,625
Do you have the guts to talk?

324
00:19:28,833 --> 00:19:31,541
- I want to fix everything.
- What do you want to fix?

325
00:19:31,750 --> 00:19:34,208
The trouble is already done.

326
00:19:34,416 --> 00:19:37,166
She deserves an honorable man
for her child.

327
00:19:37,375 --> 00:19:40,500
- Where can I find one?
- I am a honorable man!

328
00:19:40,708 --> 00:19:44,416
- I'll marry her, if you want.
- If I want?

329
00:19:44,625 --> 00:19:48,041
You should be a bit more humble
after all the problems you caused?

330
00:19:48,250 --> 00:19:50,875
Of course you have to marry her!

331
00:19:51,083 --> 00:19:53,583
But I want to know something.

332
00:19:53,791 --> 00:19:55,916
I never lost track of you.

333
00:19:56,125 --> 00:19:58,625
I always had somebody watching you.

334
00:19:58,833 --> 00:20:01,625
Explain to me how you did it?

335
00:20:01,833 --> 00:20:04,458
It's not the time.
Carmelina would get ashamed!

336
00:20:04,666 --> 00:20:08,750
- You'd get ashamed, right?
- Yes, I'm ashamed... About?

337
00:20:08,958 --> 00:20:12,833
You should've been ashamed before!
Now it's too late!

338
00:20:13,041 --> 00:20:15,583
Exactly... Too late. Very late.

339
00:20:15,791 --> 00:20:19,250
We are wasting time
with all this chatter.

340
00:20:19,458 --> 00:20:22,250
Nicolino is right,
the months go by fast.

341
00:20:22,458 --> 00:20:25,791
- They fly!
- When did this happen?

342
00:20:26,000 --> 00:20:29,666
I don't know!
Nicolino knows, he did it all!

343
00:20:29,916 --> 00:20:31,791
What is this?

344
00:20:32,000 --> 00:20:36,416
I want to see through this.
Come to Annunziata with me.

345
00:20:36,625 --> 00:20:39,666
So we can figure out the truth.

346
00:20:49,375 --> 00:20:53,583
Hurry up, Annunziata.
The baby will be born by itself!

347
00:20:53,791 --> 00:20:56,041
- The hat.
- I don't have the hat!

348
00:20:56,250 --> 00:20:59,416
- Mine!
- You need it to help give birth?

349
00:20:59,625 --> 00:21:03,583
- I am a lady!
- I'm worried!

350
00:21:03,791 --> 00:21:06,000
Calm down, we have time.

351
00:21:06,208 --> 00:21:08,500
Get out. Leave!

352
00:21:08,708 --> 00:21:11,833
My wife can't wait!

353
00:21:12,041 --> 00:21:14,041
I have to speak with you.

354
00:21:14,250 --> 00:21:18,458
You don't have to talk
to anyone, I am first.

355
00:21:18,666 --> 00:21:20,458
Wait outside, I'll be right there.

356
00:21:20,666 --> 00:21:23,458
- My child will be born by itself!
- Get out.

357
00:21:23,666 --> 00:21:26,875
Nicolino, wait.
When I come back we can talk.

358
00:21:27,083 --> 00:21:29,708
I can't wait.
Amalia and Carmelina are arriving.

359
00:21:29,916 --> 00:21:33,125
- If they find me here, I am done!
- They're coming here?

360
00:21:33,333 --> 00:21:35,375
What are they coming to do here?

361
00:21:35,583 --> 00:21:37,625
Between you and Carmelina...

362
00:21:37,833 --> 00:21:42,000
It's not what you think.
I need your help.

363
00:21:42,208 --> 00:21:47,250
How dare you?
I am an honest midwife!

364
00:21:47,458 --> 00:21:51,375
- I don't do certain things!
- Relax. What did you understand?

365
00:21:51,583 --> 00:21:54,000
You need
to help me marry Carmelina.

366
00:21:54,208 --> 00:21:56,750
You know the situation I'm in.

367
00:21:56,958 --> 00:22:00,916
- I resolved to a trick.
- What did you do?

368
00:22:01,125 --> 00:22:04,458
Me and Carmelina told that
we are expecting, but it's not true.

369
00:22:04,666 --> 00:22:09,000
I'm about to climb
Mount Calvary for you.

370
00:22:09,208 --> 00:22:12,541
- I'm climbing it.
- Mrs., don't go up!

371
00:22:12,750 --> 00:22:16,333
- Why not?
- Annunziata isn't here.

372
00:22:16,541 --> 00:22:19,541
- Did she leave?
- No, she didn't leave.

373
00:22:19,750 --> 00:22:24,833
She is not here,
but she didn't leave yet?

374
00:22:25,041 --> 00:22:28,958
- Move it, Carmelina.
- OK, go.

375
00:22:29,166 --> 00:22:31,208
Whatever happens happens.

376
00:22:31,416 --> 00:22:34,666
It's destiny,
he will be born by itself.

377
00:22:34,875 --> 00:22:38,708
- What do you want from me?
- Say that Carmelina is pregnant.

378
00:22:38,916 --> 00:22:42,541
- So we can get married.
- If she discovers everything,

379
00:22:42,750 --> 00:22:44,916
- how will I look?
- Don't worry.

380
00:22:45,125 --> 00:22:47,541
I'll fix that right away!

381
00:22:47,750 --> 00:22:51,250
Now we have to go.
Let's go.

382
00:22:52,500 --> 00:22:55,916
They're here! Go over there.

383
00:22:57,750 --> 00:23:00,875
Amalia, how are you?
How nice to see you again!

384
00:23:01,083 --> 00:23:03,541
Every day these kids are a problem.

385
00:23:03,750 --> 00:23:07,375
- What happened?
- You need to check out the girl.

386
00:23:07,583 --> 00:23:10,666
- What are you saying?
- Nothing happened!

387
00:23:10,875 --> 00:23:15,250
- It's better if I leave.
- Carmelina, come here.

388
00:23:15,458 --> 00:23:19,416
Sit here and tell me what happened.

389
00:23:19,625 --> 00:23:22,791
Open your mouth,
stick out your tongue.

390
00:23:23,791 --> 00:23:26,291
- This girl is pregnant!
- Me?

391
00:23:26,500 --> 00:23:29,708
- It's very clear!
- How? Just by looking?

392
00:23:29,916 --> 00:23:33,458
You can see with the naked eye!
The baby is in there.

393
00:23:33,666 --> 00:23:37,750
- I think it's a boy.
- It can't be true!

394
00:23:37,958 --> 00:23:40,125
Do you know more than Annunziata?

395
00:23:40,333 --> 00:23:43,458
Nicolino and I,
we haven't been alone together.

396
00:23:43,666 --> 00:23:46,208
Then it's someone else?
Who was it?

397
00:23:46,416 --> 00:23:49,500
- No one. How did it happened.
- Oh, Virgin Mary!

398
00:23:49,708 --> 00:23:51,875
Calm down, Amalia.

399
00:23:52,083 --> 00:23:55,708
Ready? For what? Without me?

400
00:23:55,916 --> 00:23:59,416
I knew it! I'll take care of it.
Congratulations, goodbye.

401
00:23:59,625 --> 00:24:02,041
Excuse me, I must tell the
poor guy who's waiting.

402
00:24:02,250 --> 00:24:04,125
- Who is it?
- The father.

403
00:24:04,333 --> 00:24:07,750
The father! It's not Nicolino?

404
00:24:07,958 --> 00:24:10,708
Wait! Where are you going?

405
00:24:11,416 --> 00:24:13,958
Carmelina! Come here.

406
00:24:14,166 --> 00:24:16,125
- Come here!
- Nicolino, I'm afraid!

407
00:24:16,333 --> 00:24:18,791
- What are you doing?
- Mrs. Annunziata is in on it.

408
00:24:19,000 --> 00:24:21,666
- You keep playing your part.
- I didn't know anything!

409
00:24:21,875 --> 00:24:24,375
- I got scared.
- It went fine.

410
00:24:24,583 --> 00:24:26,583
You're the father.

411
00:24:26,791 --> 00:24:30,541
- It was you!
- What are you doing?

412
00:24:32,958 --> 00:24:37,041
- What father?
- One moment!

413
00:24:37,250 --> 00:24:40,708
- This is the other father.
- What are you talking about?

414
00:24:40,916 --> 00:24:44,708
Please, relax, calm!
It's a beautiful girl.

415
00:24:44,916 --> 00:24:46,958
That one? She was going to eat me!

416
00:24:47,166 --> 00:24:50,333
No! Not her! You are a father,
I just found out.

417
00:24:50,541 --> 00:24:53,666
You were all in on it!

418
00:24:53,875 --> 00:24:56,041
Stay calm, I am the father.

419
00:24:56,250 --> 00:24:58,833
Nicolino, you're here!
So who is this man?

420
00:24:59,041 --> 00:25:00,875
He was having a child.

421
00:25:01,083 --> 00:25:04,875
- OK, but the real father is me.
- Yes, the real father is him.

422
00:25:05,083 --> 00:25:08,208
What did you say? Repeat it!

423
00:25:08,416 --> 00:25:11,958
- I'll kill you!
- Stop!

424
00:25:12,166 --> 00:25:14,708
How disgusting!
Let's review the situation.

425
00:25:14,916 --> 00:25:16,916
You are the father of your child.

426
00:25:17,125 --> 00:25:21,625
- He is the father of another child!
- Good!

427
00:25:21,833 --> 00:25:24,500
My daughter has only one father
and that father is me!

428
00:25:24,708 --> 00:25:26,666
- Let's hope!
- No, it's me.

429
00:25:26,875 --> 00:25:29,041
Go to your daughter.

430
00:25:29,250 --> 00:25:32,166
Let them get married right away.

431
00:25:32,375 --> 00:25:35,125
- Hurry up.
- Get married right away.

432
00:25:35,333 --> 00:25:38,458
Come back to me
when it's the right time.

433
00:25:38,666 --> 00:25:41,083
- Do you understand?
- Of course.

434
00:25:41,291 --> 00:25:43,916
- Thank you.
- You're welcome.

435
00:25:47,041 --> 00:25:49,750
Relax, Nicolino.
These are the last sacrifices.

436
00:25:49,958 --> 00:25:51,791
It's humiliating

437
00:25:52,000 --> 00:25:57,041
but Maria is going to take care
of the documents for our marriage.

438
00:26:02,958 --> 00:26:06,041
- Send us the documents right away!
- Don't worry.

439
00:26:06,250 --> 00:26:09,083
- I'll hurry up.
- May the Lord guide you.

440
00:26:09,291 --> 00:26:12,625
Every day that goes by,
the problem gets bigger!

441
00:26:12,833 --> 00:26:14,416
Here, it's done.

442
00:26:15,958 --> 00:26:18,666
Aunt Maria, your bags are loaded.
You can leave!

443
00:26:18,875 --> 00:26:22,750
- You're even being funny!
- Should I start crying?

444
00:26:22,958 --> 00:26:26,083
Amalia, don't get upset,
he is an unresponsive man!

445
00:26:26,291 --> 00:26:30,875
Worry about the documents.
Send them right away.

446
00:26:31,083 --> 00:26:34,125
Carmelina's honor is in your hands!

447
00:26:34,333 --> 00:26:36,958
Mom, do you want to tell everyone?

448
00:26:37,166 --> 00:26:39,875
I'm not like you and Nicolino!

449
00:26:40,083 --> 00:26:42,833
This story has made me tired.
I feel nauseous!

450
00:26:43,041 --> 00:26:46,000
- Nicolino, you are going to vomit!
- What do you want?

451
00:26:46,208 --> 00:26:48,083
Don't worry, I'm not sick.

452
00:26:48,291 --> 00:26:51,041
I have two children,
I'm more of an expert than you.

453
00:26:51,250 --> 00:26:54,000
In your condition,
you should have nausea.

454
00:26:54,208 --> 00:26:56,750
Leave me alone.

455
00:26:57,875 --> 00:27:01,083
If mom says you have nausea,
you have nausea.

456
00:27:01,291 --> 00:27:04,416
- Really?
- Yes. Mom is always right.

457
00:27:11,541 --> 00:27:13,958
Don't worry, this will help you.

458
00:27:14,166 --> 00:27:18,250
- Mom, I feel something here.
- What is it?

459
00:27:18,458 --> 00:27:21,708
- I am craving strawberries.
- Strawberries?

460
00:27:21,916 --> 00:27:23,625
Wait a second.

461
00:27:25,000 --> 00:27:26,875
Yes, strawberries.

462
00:27:27,625 --> 00:27:31,625
- I'll send someone to get them.
- Mom, they are expensive!

463
00:27:31,833 --> 00:27:35,583
I don't care. Nicolino has to
learn what it means to be a father!

464
00:27:38,166 --> 00:27:42,000
Go buy half a kilo of strawberries,
Carmelina is craving them.

465
00:27:42,208 --> 00:27:44,750
- Strawberries?
- Are you sure?

466
00:27:44,958 --> 00:27:48,708
- Yes, strawberries!
- Not oranges or clementines?

467
00:27:48,916 --> 00:27:51,666
No. Go. It can't be born
craving strawberries!

468
00:27:51,875 --> 00:27:55,625
I'm going to get strawberries
for Carmelina.

469
00:27:55,833 --> 00:27:57,708
Good boy.

470
00:28:01,375 --> 00:28:03,458
- Nicolino, good morning.
- Good morning!

471
00:28:03,666 --> 00:28:06,125
I'm going, Carmelina
is craving strawberries.

472
00:28:06,333 --> 00:28:08,708
She has a craving,
also Mrs. Amalia told me.

473
00:28:08,916 --> 00:28:11,208
The baby is due in spring, right?

474
00:28:11,416 --> 00:28:16,750
What? Many springs may come
but nothing will come out!

475
00:28:16,958 --> 00:28:22,333
What?
